# Client Expense & Revenue Tracker (UI)

## Project Context

Dashboard for tracking client expenses and revenue across quarterly, yearly, and custom date ranges. Primary users: freelancers/agencies reviewing financial performance per client. UI should feel clean, trustworthy, and data-forward — like Stripe Dashboard or Linear, not a spreadsheet.

## Tech Stack (use these; don't introduce alternatives without asking)

- **Framework:** Next.js (App Router) + TypeScript
- **Styling:** Tailwind CSS
- **Components:** shadcn/ui (Radix primitives)
- **Charts:** Recharts (revenue vs expense trends)
- **Icons:** lucide-react
- **Forms:** react-hook-form + zod
- **Tables:** @tanstack/react-table
- **State/data:** TanStack Query for server state; React state for local UI
- **Dates:** date-fns (never moment.js)

## Color System — Light Theme (default)

- Base: `white` / `slate-50`
- Surfaces: `white`, `border-slate-200`, `shadow-sm`
- Text: `slate-900` primary, `slate-500` muted
- Accent: `indigo-600` — buttons, active nav, key highlights (use sparingly)
- Revenue / positive → `emerald-600` text, `emerald-50` bg tint
- Expenses / negative → `rose-600` text, `rose-50` bg tint
- Net / neutral → `slate-900`
- Always pair color with `+`/`-` or icons — never color alone
- No pure `#000` / `#FFF` pairs; use slate scale
- **No dark mode in v1** unless explicitly requested

## Layout

- Sidebar nav + top bar with date-range / quarter selector
- Dashboard: KPI cards → trend charts → detail tables
- 8px spacing scale; cards: `rounded-xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-6 shadow-sm`
- Max width ~1280px (`max-w-7xl`), centered, generous whitespace

## Data Display

- Currency via `Intl.NumberFormat` — use `@/lib/format/currency`
- KPI cards: compact notation (`$12.4K`); tables/tooltips: full precision
- Quarter/year toggles: segmented control or tabs (not dropdown for ≤5 options)
- Tables: sticky header, right-align numbers, subtle `even:bg-slate-50`
- Charts: gridlines `slate-100`, tooltips white + `slate-200` border

## Components

- One component per file; route-specific components colocated with route
- Extend shadcn via `className` + `cn()` — don't fork primitives
- `focus-visible:` on all interactive elements
- Loading: skeleton loaders matching layout — not spinners for cards/tables
- Empty states: friendly message + CTA

## Accessibility

- WCAG AA contrast minimum
- Charts: `aria-label` or text/table fallback
- Forms: visible labels, `aria-describedby` on validation errors

## General

- Responsive to ~375px; optimize for desktop/tablet
- Composition over prop-drilling; shared card/table/chart patterns in `components/`
- Tailwind only + `cn()` — no inline styles
